          q: "The 10g monofilament should never be tested over which area, as it produces a falsely reassuring result?",
          options: ["The heel", "Areas of callus", "The dorsal foot", "Between the toes"],
          answer: 1,
          explain: "Callus should never be tested, since thickened skin reduces sensitivity to the monofilament regardless of the underlying nerve function, producing a falsely reassuring (normal-seeming) result that does not reflect true protective sensation status."
