      { q: "In a previously well-controlled patient, new-onset unexplained hyperglycaemia alongside a foot ulcer should raise suspicion of:", opts: ["Improved wound healing","Occult infection","Resolving neuropathy","Over-treatment with insulin"], a: 1, exp: "New-onset hyperglycaemia in a previously controlled patient can be the only clue to an occult diabetic foot infection, because classical signs such as warmth, erythema and pain are frequently blunted by neuropathy and impaired immune response." }
