          q: "Ankle equinus is defined as dorsiflexion restricted below which lunge test measurement?",
          options: ["10-15mm", "20-25mm", "35-40mm", "50-55mm"],
          answer: 2,
          explain: "Ankle equinus is defined as restricted dorsiflexion below 10 degrees from neutral, or below 35-40mm on the standardised lunge test — carrying the strongest documented association with plantar fasciopathy of any single structural risk factor."
