          answer: 1,
          explain: "Functional hallux limitus shows restricted dorsiflexion specifically under weight-bearing load, despite normal or near-normal non-weight-bearing range — commonly driven by excessive STJ pronation. Structural hallux limitus shows genuine restriction in both positions, typically reflecting osteoarthritic change."
