          explain: "Congenital absence or hypoplasia of the dorsalis pedis occurs in approximately 8-12% of the population, with the posterior tibial artery providing compensatory supply via the plantar arch — meaning an absent dorsalis pedis pulse may reflect normal variation rather than pathological occlusion."
