          q: "Sensory loss confined specifically to the first dorsal web space most strongly localises to which nerve?",
          options: ["Superficial peroneal nerve", "Deep peroneal nerve", "Sural nerve", "Saphenous nerve"],
          answer: 1,
          explain: "The deep peroneal nerve provides sensory innervation to a small, well-defined area of the first dorsal web space specifically. This makes isolated sensory change in this exact location a useful clinical landmark for localising deep peroneal nerve involvement."
