          q: "The lunula, the visible white crescent at the nail base, represents the visible portion of which structure?",
          options: ["The nail bed", "The distal matrix", "The hyponychium", "The eponychium"],
          answer: 1,
          explain: "The lunula represents the visible portion of the distal matrix. The proximal matrix (not visible) produces the dorsal nail plate layers, while the distal matrix, visible as the lunula, produces the ventral layers."
