          answer: 1,
          explain: "Pathergy is the defining feature of pyoderma gangrenosum — tissue trauma, including debridement, triggers paradoxical worsening and rapid wound expansion. Debridement should be withheld pending specialist assessment in any wound with suspicious features (violaceous, undermined margins, disproportionate pain, rapid progression)."
