          answer: 1,
          explain: "Reactive tendinopathy, the acute proliferative response to sudden overload, is generally most responsive to load management and most likely to fully reverse with appropriate intervention, compared with the more structurally disorganised dysrepair and degenerative stages further along the continuum."
