          explain: "Beyer et al. (2015, AJSM) found HSR achieved 83% patient satisfaction compared with 67% for eccentric loading, despite equivalent 12-month pain and function outcomes — a clinically important finding given satisfaction's link to real-world adherence and outcomes."
