          answer: 1,
          explain: "Riddle et al. (2003, JBJS) identified ankle equinus as the single strongest independent predictor of plantar fasciopathy, with an odds ratio of 23.3 — substantially exceeding elevated BMI (OR 5.6) as the most powerful single structural risk factor identified."
